<F P=101> Poland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Sejm Votes To Accept `Strategy for Poland' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Sejm Votes To Accept `Strategy for Poland' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406122794 Warsaw PAP in English 1207 GMT 24 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2406122794 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, June 24 -- The government won the vote in 
the Sejm on Friday on acceptance of its information on the 
"Strategy for Poland" by 244 votes for acceptance, 87 for 
rejection, 13 abstentions and 116 not voting. The "strategy" is 
the government's economic programme for the years 1994-97. 
  Deputies from the government coalition parties, the 
Democratic Left Alliance (SLD) and the Polish Peasant Party 
(PSL) voted for acceptance as did two Union of Labour (UP), one 
Non-Party Reform Bloc (BBWR) and one independent deputy. No 
deputy from the Freedom Union (UW), the Confederation for an 
Independent Poland (KPN), the German minority or the Polish 
Socialist Party voted for accepting the information. 

</TEXT>

