<H3> <TI>   Freedom Union Chooses Warsaw Candidate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Freedom Union Chooses Warsaw Candidate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806190694 Warsaw PAP in English 1759 GMT 28 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2806190694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, June 28 -- The Freedom Union (UW) has 
forwarded Michal Boni, former labour minister in the Jan 
Krzysztof Bielecki government, as its candidate for the 
president of Warsaw, it was announced on Tuesday. 
  The Warsaw chapter of the Social-Democracy of the Republic 
of 
Poland (SDRP) declared its willingness for talks, but did not 
take a stand on Boni's candidature. The coalition of the 
Democratic Left Alliance (SLD) and the Polish Peasant Party 
(PSL) has won 29 out of 85 seats in the Warsaw Council. 
  The SDRP will decide about the UW candidature after it 
learns 
the answer for its conditions presented in the talks the party 
is conducting now. If they are not met, the SDRP threatens it 
will boycott the election of the president of Warsaw who is 
chosen in the presence of at least two thirds of councillors. 
  Warsaw SDRP said that the number of seats won in the local 
government elections obliges the SLD-PSL coaliton to care for 
the city. The party wants to have one third of seats in the 
Warsaw local government assembly. 
  Leader of the Warsaw chapter of the SDRP Andrzej Zelazowski 
said that his party is conducting unofficial talks with 
representatives of other political groups except the right-wing 
parties about eventual coalitions in local government. 

</TEXT>

