<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Poland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ministry Backs Quick Ratification of Concordat </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Ministry Backs Quick Ratification of Concordat </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2806200594 Warsaw PAP in English 1952 GMT 28 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2806200594 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, June 28 -- The Foreign Ministry is 
supporting the fast ratification of the concordat between the 
Vatican and the Republic of Poland, a department director at the 
ministry Janusz Stanczyk said at a press conference organized in 
Warsaw Tuesday before the first reading of the draft 
ratification law to take place in the Sejm on June 30. 
  Stanczyk recalled Foreign Minister Andrzej Olechowski's 
speech in the Sejm in May on Polish foreign policy, in which the 
minister favoured the fast ratification of the concordat since 
otherwise "Polish relations with the Holy See would enter a 
difficult stage." Stanczyk refused to comment on whether the 
rejection of the concordat by the Sejm would result in the 
recalling of the Polish ambassador to the Vatican. 
  Asked whether it will be possible to negotiate another 
concordat if the present one is rejected Stanczyk said that such 
a possibility exists in legal terms but one cannot be sure if 
the Holy See would be interested in "repeating the uncertain 
procedure". 
  According to Stanczak the government is of the opinion that 
there is no incompatibility between the concordat and the 
constitution so the motion of the Democratic Left Alliance to 
postpone the ratification debate until the new constitution is 
signed is not justified. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-32765 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "dreeu125__a94032" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-EEU-94-125-A </AU>
Daily Report 
<DATE1>  24 Jun 1994 </DATE1>

