<F P=100> ANNEX </F>
<F P=101> Poland </F>
<H3> <TI>   Romanian Foreign Minister Visits, Comments </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Romanian Foreign Minister Visits, Comments </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   LD2406143694 Warsaw PAP in English 1338 GMT 24 Jun 94 -- FOR 
OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> LD2406143694 </F>
<F P=104>  Warsaw PAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Warsaw, June 23--Poland and Romania are natural 
partners with similar strategic goals and common security 
interests, Romanian Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Minister 
Teodor Melescanu told a press conference in Warsaw on Friday. 
According to him, both countries may cooperate in economy, 
tourism, communications and on third markets. 
  Speaking about his two-day visit to Poland, Melescanu said 
that it aimed to develop cooperation between the two countries, 
especially between the Polish and Romanian parliaments. He said 
that the Romanian president will visit Poland this autumn. 
Polish Prime Minister Waldemar Pawlak has also been invited to 
visit Romania but the date has not been fixed yet. 
  During his visit Melescanu has presented some concrete 
proposals how to boost mutual cooperation. He talked about the 
reconstruction of an old railway route connecting the two 
countries and setting up a Polish-Romanian tourist enterprise. 
Melescanu thinks that such projects could be supported by the 
European Union. 
  Speaking about Romanian debt to Poland now amounting to 50 
million transfer roubles, the Romanian minister said that his 
country will pay it off. He also hoped that any delays will not 
hamper economic cooperation of the two countries which are of 
similar size and which have similar problems. 
  In the morning, the Romanian guest laid flowers at the grave 
of Jozef Beck, Poland's pre-war foreign minister who died during 
the Second World War in Romania. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

