<H3> <TI>   PDAR Withdraws Support For Ruling Party </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    PDAR Withdraws Support For Ruling Party </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   AU2806173794 Bucharest ROMPRES in English 1418 GMT 28 Jun 94 
-- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> AU2806173794 </F>
<F P=104>  Bucharest ROMPRES </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 28/6/1994 -- The Agrarian 
Democratic Party of Romania [PDAR], whose representation in 
Romania's Parliament is ensured by only five parliamentarians, 
has decided to withdraw its support given so far to the ruling 
Party of Social Democracy, told a news conference PDAR leader 
Victor Surdu, on 28 June. 
  Also, he said the Agrarian parliamentarians "will take 
advantage" of the debate of the opposition's no-confidence 
motion in order to present their stand on their own, while 
shunning certain "opinions" of the opposition. The PDAR leader 
said that the no-confidence motion promoted by the Democratic 
Convention ignored certain achievements of the ruling party. 
The PDAR will back it though. 

</TEXT>

