<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Bucharest, ROMPRES, 28/06/1994 -- The censure 
motion against the Vacaroiu Cabinet laid by the Democratic 
Agrarian Party of Romania [PDAR] is "a very big error," said 
Adrian Nastase, executive president of the ruling Party of 
Social Democracy [PDSR], at a press conference on Tuesday [28 
June]. 
  The PSDR leader said that the PDAR Leader Victor Surdu was 
attempting "to draw the electorate of his party onto a certain 
zone in order to justify the PDAR shift to opposition." Anyway, 
the ruling PSDR will treat the PDAR "as an opposition party with 
all the consequences resulting thereof," said Adrian Nastase. 

</TEXT>

