  [Editorial Report] Buenos Aires LA NACION in Spanish on 13 
May publishes on page 21 an unattributed 200-word article on an 
agreement between Corrientes Province and Russia. The article 
says: "Corrientes Governor Raul Romero Feris and Russian Trade 
Representative Anatoliy Timoschenko signed a protocol to promote 
and enhance integration and review trade possibilities." The 
article says: "Russian entrepreneurs are interested in raw 
materials, including oranges, lemons, rice, meat, and various 
types of hides, and Corrientes Province is interested in road 
maintenance and electric equipment." The article concludes by 
stating: "Romero Feris expressed the province's interest in the 
participation of Russian enterprises in energy market 
operations." 

