<H3> <TI>   University Seniors To Have Jobs Upon Graduating </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    University Seniors To Have Jobs Upon Graduating </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3105005194 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 1407 GMT 30 May 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA3105005194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 30 May (PL) -- The president of the 
Federation of University Students [FEU], Otto Rivero, confirmed 
today that the approximately 8,000 students who will graduate 
this year from Cuba's universities have job guarantees despite 
Cuba's adverse economic situation. 
  Rivero said the conclusion of the school year is less than 
45 
days away and already 7,000 graduating university seniors have 
been informed where they will have a job. There are ongoing 
talks with authorities to determine where the rest will work. 
Rivero said a great effort is being made to guarantee jobs for 
all graduating students. 
  Cuba is enduring severe economic difficulties following the 
loss of its main foreign markets as a result of the 
disappearance of the socialist camp in Europe and of the Soviet 
Union and as a result also of the tightened economic blockade 
imposed on Cuba by the United States more than three decades ago. 

</TEXT>

