<H3> <TI>   Defense Committees Urge Support for Measures </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Defense Committees Urge Support for Measures </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2905174894 Havana PRENSA LATINA in Spanish 2116 GMT 28 May 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PA2905174894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana PRENSA LATINA </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 28 May (PL) -- The National Directorate of 
the Committees for the Defense of the Revolution (CDR), the 
largest people's organization in Cuba, today called on the 
population to support the measures adopted to cleanse the 
national economy and increase surveillance against crime. 
  Sixto Batista Santana, national CDR coordinator, called on 
CDR members to contribute to achieving an understanding for and 
to support the measures, so as to overcome the economic 
difficulties that have appeared following the collapse of the 
socialist bloc and the worsening of Washington's blockade. 
  The main leader of the CDR, created 33 years ago, presided 
over the second meeting of the CDR National Directorate in which 
surveillance by CDR members in every block of the country was 
analyzed as an important factor to prevent crime, according to a 
wire item reported today by the National Information Agency. 
  At the meeting, it was agreed to recognize the work of 
prominent CDR members in performing their tasks and the mission 
of explaining to the population the new financial provisions, 
the source indicated. The Council of State decreed an increase 
in the price of some products, such as cigarettes, beer, rum, 
and such services as electricity and urban transportation, as 
well as general payment for water service. 
  During the semester from October 1993 to March of this year, 
CDR members from all over the country contributed 243,068 
voluntary blood donations, donated over 11 million crystal 
containers, 8,000 tons of paper and carton, and 2,587 tons of 
aluminum, in a contribution they make each year to public health 
and the national economy. 

</TEXT>

