<H3> <TI>   Single Command of Judicial Police Confirmed </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Single Command of Judicial Police Confirmed </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2705175594 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0430 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2705175594 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "24 Hours" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Today, Attorney General Humberto Benitez Trevino 
said the Federal Judicial Police [PJF] has only one command and 
this will prevent corruption. Mr. Benitez Trevino made this 
statement as he replied to charges by some Catholic Church 
leaders who claim that agents in the PGR [Attorney General's 
Office] are involved in drug trafficking. 
  [Begin Benitez recording] Beginning yesterday, there is only 
one command in the PJF. This is the start of the reorganization 
of the police. [end recording] 
  Interviewed at the end of the first Ibero-American Congress 
on Copyrights, he said the entry of government employees into 
the PGR has been limited. 
  [Begin Benitez recording] The only way to obtain employment 
in the PJF, professional police service, or the PGR will be, 
solely and exclusively, through the Professional Training 
Institute. [end recording] 
  He reiterated that in the fight against corruption, no one 
is 
above the law. Benitez also admitted that crime has increased 5 
percent in the Federal District over the past four months. 

</TEXT>

