<H3> <TI>   Press Release on Occupation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Press Release on Occupation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2905212694 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 1700 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2905212694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Sunday Supplemental NTV" newscast] </F>
  [Text] It has been reported in a press release that a group 
of people illegally entered the residence of His Excellency Paul 
Vermeirsch, the Belgian ambassador to Cuba, on the morning of 28 
May in an attempt to push for their departure from Cuba. 
  This new incident is another consequence of the calls to 
illegality made by counterrevolutionary stations broadcasting 
from Miami and, basically, the result of the restrictive 
policies implemented by U.S. immigration authorities who 
continue to block legal procedures for people wanting to 
emigrate to the United States. 
  These people resort to illegal and even violent means to 
depart the country after repeatedly failing to obtain visas. 
The revolutionary government, which does not obstruct those who 
comply with the legal procedures for departing Cuba, has 
reiterated, on several occasions, its commitment to not allowing 
the use of illegal break-ins into diplomatic missions in Cuba as 
a mean of leaving the country. 

</TEXT>

