<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Postpones Increase in Fuel Prices </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government Postpones Increase in Fuel Prices </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3105040094 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 0245 GMT 31 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA3105040094 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Havana, 30 May (NOTIMEX) -- The Cuban Government 
announced tonight that it will postpone the increase in the 
price of fuel that was to become effective on Wednesday, as 
established in an official agreement. 
  According to a communique released by the Finance and Prices 
Ministry [name of ministry as received], the decision was made 
because private automobile owners still have gasoline ration 
cards that were distributed months ago. 
  The government decided that "during June, prices and sale 
conditions for such ration cards will be the same as those that 
were in effect prior" to the 20 May official agreement, the 
communique noted. The Finance and Price Ministry, however, did 
not indicate if the price increase will go in effect in July or 
at a later date. 
  Private automobile owners have restricted access to gasoline 
through ration cards that are distributed by gasoline 
distributors periodically. Up to 1991, consumers received cards 
that allowed them to purchase up to 230 liters of gasoline each 
quarter. The quota has dropped progressively since then however. 
Ration cards for 20 liters were distributed in April and ration 
cards for this month were for a similar quantity. 
  Premium gasoline will rise from 38 cents to 1.20 pesos per 
liter and regular gasoline will go from 28 cents to 1 peso. A 
Cuban peso is equivalent to one dollar but the local currency is 
exchanged at a rate of 100 pesos per dollar at the black market. 
  In addition to gasoline, the government approved increases 
for the prices of cigarettes and rum, as well as all 
transportation fares. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS4-32814 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat104_a_94007" </HT>


<HEADER>
