<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Stresses NAM's Importance </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Stresses NAM's Importance </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL3005190194 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1700 
GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3005190194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina met several 
officials in Cairo early this morning, including Zimbabwean 
Foreign Minister Nathan Shamuyarira, Vietnamese Foreign Minister 
Nguyen Manh Cam, and Arab League Secretary General Issmat 'Abd 
al-Majid. 
  Upon arriving in Cairo last night, Robaina emphasized that 
although times are not the same as 40 years ago, the Nonaligned 
Movement [NAM] maintains its importance. Robaina pointed out 
that NAM members have the right to be heard in the concert of 
nations since the organization encompasses more than two-thirds 
of mankind. He added that this right can be justified today more 
than ever due to increasing international instability, the 
emergence of a militarily and politically unilateral world, and 
the concentration of economic power in the countries of the 
North. 
  Robaina said: This is more than enough reason to attend a 
meeting such as this, with the interest of not only establishing 
positions but also putting things into motion. The meetings for 
experts, who will discuss the topics to be covered by the 
foreign ministers beginning tomorrow, began this morning. 

</TEXT>

