<H3> <TI>   National Assembly President Concludes UK Visit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    National Assembly President Concludes UK Visit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL3005170294 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1405 GMT 
30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3005170294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ricardo Alarcon, president of the National Assembly 
of the People's Government, ANPP, has concluded a visit to the 
UK at the invitation of the British group of the 
Interparliamentary Union. In London, Alarcon met with numerous 
British parliamentarians on Cuba's current situation and on the 
particularities of its government system. Alarcon met Betty 
Boothroyd, president of the House of Commons, among other 
figures. 
  Alarcon began his visit to the UK on 23 May as head of a 
delegation that included Osvaldo Martinez, president of the ANPP 
Economic Commission, and Lidia Tablada, director of the National 
Center for Agricultural-Livestock Hygiene. The Cuban delegation 
led by Ricardo Alarcon also met UK authorities, including (David 
Hitchcock), the state minister of the Foreign Office. It was 
decided at the meeting that the British Government would send an 
official delegation to Cuba, to be led by (Patrick Glovlin), 
state minister for trade and technology and a participant of the 
meetings with Alarcon in London. 
  The Cuban parliamentary delegation also met British 
businessmen interested in maintaining and strengthening trade 
relations with Cuba. Coinciding with Alarcon's visit, Basic 
Industry Minister Marcos Portal was also in London and held 
several meetings with British businessmen. 

</TEXT>

