<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Civil Defense Assesses Flood Damage in Provinces </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Civil Defense Assesses Flood Damage in Provinces </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2805153494 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1401 GMT 
28 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2805153494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] The Civil Defense has made a final assessment of the 
damage, encompassing an area of over 40,000 square km, caused by 
heavy rainfall in the eastern provinces. Most of the damage 
took place in the provinces of Santiago de Cuba, Guantanamo, and 
Camaguey. The damage includes the partial or complete 
destruction of 4,360 houses and damages to another 32,720. Over 
250,000 people were affected by the recent rains and floods. A 
significant number of dams, aqueducts, and electric and 
telephone services were also damaged. Damages were also 
reported in 4,500 square km of crops, mainly sugarcane, rice, 
tubers, and vegetables. 

</TEXT>

