<F P=100> Honduras </F>
<H3> <TI>   Foreign Minister Announces Joining of NAM </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Foreign Minister Announces Joining of NAM </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2605205394 Mexico City NOTIMEX in Spanish 1740 GMT 26 May 
94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2605205394 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City NOTIMEX </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tegucigalpa, 26 May (NOTIMEX) -- Honduras will 
officially join the Nonaligned Movement (NAM) on 30 May, Foreign 
Minister Ernesto Paz Aguilar confirmed today. In remarks to 
NOTIMEX, Paz explained that Honduras was not allowed into the 
NAM during the past decade, when the country served as a base of 
operations for the Nicaraguan contras who were fighting the 
Sandinist regime. The official indicated that the nonaligned 
countries agreed to let Honduras join its ranks in the wake of 
the inauguration of President Carlos Roberto Reina, who is 
regarded as a leader of social democratic ideas and defender of 
human rights. 
  Paz, who will be the first Honduran foreign minister to 
participate in a meeting of that organization, said that he will 
attend the NAM conference with an "optimistic" attitude and that 
the conference will be held from 30 May to 6 June in Cairo, 
Egypt. 
  He added that he will attend the meeting with confidence 
that 
the new realities ruling the world will provide just and 
equitable participation to the Third World countries in that 
international movement. 

</TEXT>

