BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 27 May (NA) -- The Foreign Ministry 
reported today that two Argentine citizens are being held 
"hostage" in the Techint Company offices in the Bolivian town of 
Camiri which has been blocked as part of a civic strike over 
salary hike demands. 
  The Argentine citizens are engineers Jose Gasparoni and Juan 
Quevedo. The Argentine Foreign Ministry is conducting intense 
negotiations with the Bolivian Government over Gasparoni and 
Quevedo. 
  In this regard, Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella called his 
Bolivian counterpart to personally inquire about the situation 
of these two citizens while the Foreign Ministry has called the 
Techint Company in our country and is calling the engineers' 
relatives. 

