<H3> <TI>   UCR, Grand Front To Reject Re-Election of Governors </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UCR, Grand Front To Reject Re-Election of Governors </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY3105132594 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1826 GMT 30 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY3105132594 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe, 30 May (NA) -- Raul Alfonsin, leader of 
the Radical [Radical Civic Union -- UCR] bloc, and Carlos Chacho 
Alvarez, head of the Grand Front bloc, have agreed that the 
political forces they head will reject any government project to 
include a clause that allows the re-election of governors in the 
new constitution. 
  Alfonsin and Alvarez met at the seat of the Litoral 
University, where the Constituent Assembly will formally begin 
its sessions at 1700. 

</TEXT>

