<F P=100> Paraguay </F>
<H3> <TI>   Explains Remarks to Congress President </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Explains Remarks to Congress President </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2705200394 Asuncion Cerro Cora Sistema Nacional de 
Television Network in Spanish 1600 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2705200394 </F>
<F P=104>  Asuncion Cerro Cora Sistema Nacional de 
Television Network </F>

<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] President Juan Carlos Wasmosy has sent a letter to 
Congress President Evelio Fernandez Arevalos explaining the real 
meaning of his remarks to an Argentine newspaper with respect to 
the dissolution of Congress. 
  The president has just sent a note to Fernandez saying that 
the declarations appearing in newspapers saying that he would do 
his utmost not to dissolve Congress do not reflect what he 
honestly thinks. 
  Asked about the matter, Senator Evelio Fernandez Arevalo 
said 
he was satisfied with the president's explanation: 
  [Begin recording] The note has persuaded me. I think, as I 
said before, there has been a mistake in the way he expressed 
himself or in the transcription of his remarks. I could not 
imagine the president experiencing an internal struggle to 
prevent the dissolution of Congress. I said earlier that I could 
not conceive of anyone having a hidden agenda to provoke such a 
negative thing. 
  The note that the president had the deference to send me, I 
must admit, puts things in the right perspective. I think we 
must consider the episode closed. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

