<F P=100> Colombia </F>
<H3> <TI>   ELN Guerrillas Kill Official </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    ELN Guerrillas Kill Official </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA3005195494 Paris AFP in Spanish 1653 GMT 30 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA3005195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 30 May (AFP) -- This Monday, 
Army of National Liberation (ELN) guerrillas ambushed and killed 
Santiago Angarita, a community leader in the Colombian town of 
Convencion, Norte de Santander, from whom the rebels seized 
voting cards from this Sunday's presidential elections and 
burned them. 
  Radio reports from Santa Fe de Bogota stated Angarita was 
intercepted on his way to the National Civil Registry of Cucuta, 
a provincial capital bordering Venezuela. The guerrillas 
stripped Angarita of the sealed ballot box and then killed him. 
  The community leader transported the votes cast at the 
Municipalities of San Jose, Las Pitas, and Cartagenita and the 
town of Convencion. 
  Presidential elections held this Sunday in Colombia resulted 
in a virtual tie between Liberal Party candidate Ernesto Samper 
and Conservative Party candidate Andres Pastrana, who will vie 
in a runoff election on Sunday, 19 June. 

</TEXT>

