<H3> <TI>   Skirmishes, Minor Problems Reported </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Skirmishes, Minor Problems Reported </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2905212894 Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network in 
Spanish 1822 GMT 29 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2905212894 </F>
<F P=104>  Santa Fe de Bogota Emisoras Caracol Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota -- Presumed terrorists of the 
National Guerrilla Coordinating Board [CNG] burned three 
vehicles, two armed skirmishes between Army troops and 
subversives of the FARC [Revolutionary Armed Forces of 
Colombia], and other isolated incidents such as difficulties in 
transferring electoral officials in southern Bolivar Department, 
where new elections could be called, are the only incidents so 
far in relation to the democratic event taking place today in 
Colombia [7-second break in reception] analyzing the situation 
in the Municipalities of San Pablo and Simiti, where elections 
could not start, but in the rest of the country the situation is 
completely normal. 
  Meanwhile, the Joint Operations Command of the Military 
Forces confirmed that three interdepartmental buses were 
attacked and burned by CNG subversives on the Trunk Highway 
between Riohacha and Santa Marta. 
  The Army killed three presumed FARC members in the rural 
area 
of Baraya, Huila Department. Meanwhile, in [name indistinct] 
another column of that subversive group ambushed an Army patrol 
and wounded a soldier. 

</TEXT>

