<H3> <TI>   Air Force To Purchase 4 Skyhawk A-4M Planes </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Air Force To Purchase 4 Skyhawk A-4M Planes </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY2605233394 Buenos Aires LA NACION in Spanish 26 May 94 p 
11 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> PY2605233394 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires LA NACION </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Excerpt] In addition to the 36 Skyhawk A-4M planes already 
purchased from the United States, Argentina has decided to 
purchase four more of the planes. 
  The reason for increasing the purchase operation is that 
Argentina is interested in having inexpensive spare parts. If 
Argentina purchased spare parts on the international market, 
they would be more costly. 
  This has been confirmed by Defense Ministry sources who 
reported the existence of a letter Defense Minister Oscar 
Camilion sent to U.S. Ambassador James Cheek. [passage omitted] 

</TEXT>

