<H3> <TI>   Government-URNG Peace Talks Conclude in Puebla </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Government-URNG Peace Talks Conclude in Puebla </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2805023094 Guatemala City Televisiete Television in 
Spanish 0400 GMT 26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2805023094 </F>
<F P=104>  Guatemala City Televisiete Television </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Channel 7 News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The Guatemalan Government and the National 
Guatemalan Revolutionary Unity have outlined the guidelines for 
a national effort to solve in the short term the problem those 
persons displaced by the war, UN mediator Jean Arnoult has 
reported. 
  On Wednesday, the delegates concluded four days of debates 
in 
Puebla, Mexico, on the resettlement of the displaced. The sides 
have decided to resume the talks next week and reach a 
definitive agreement on the subject. 
  The mediator has announced the postponement of the round of 
talks slated to be held from 31 May to 3 June in Oslo, Norway, 
where the creation of a commission to investigate human rights 
violations during the three-decades-long war will be discussed. 

</TEXT>

