<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Preliminary Returns Show Samper With Slight Lead </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2905230794 Paris AFP in Spanish 2237 GMT 29 May 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2905230794 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Santa Fe de Bogota, 29 May (AFP) -- After counting 8 
percent of the 
voting tables, the first, preliminary, official returns of the 
Colombian presidential elections held today show Liberal 
presidential candidate Ernesto Samper as having a slight lead 
over his Conservative opponent Andres Pastrana. 
  After tallying 3,916 polling tables of the 47,000 throughout 
the country, Samper garnered 201,530 votes (47 percent) while 
Pastrana obtained 183,846 (42.8 percent). 

</TEXT>

