<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Discusses Goals of Movement </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Discusses Goals of Movement </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL0106015094 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0000 GMT 1 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL0106015094 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the NTV newscast] </F>
  [Excerpt] [passage omitted] On 31 May, Foreign Minister 
Roberto Robaina stated the main goal of the Nonaligned Movement 
[NAM] is to promote the economic and social development of the 
Third World. During his address to the 11th ministerial summit 
of the NAM, Robaina stressed that an opulent North and an 
impoverished South is the world's reality today. He added that 
if we sit on our hands, we are condemned to disappear, which 
would mean the disappearance of two thirds of mankind. Robaina 
affirmed that Cuba believes that the best guarantee for a 
permanent and lasting peace is the elimination of hunger. Only 
then will human rights bloom for all people rather than for a 
minuscule portion of mankind. 
  Robaina affirmed that despite the over 30-year-old blockade 
against Cuba, the Cuban people will overcome this difficult 
junction, thanks, above all, to the solidarity of the NAM. 
  Robaina continues to fulfill a busy schedule that includes 
meeting with representatives of Libya, the PRC, Cyprus, Panama, 
Zambia, Colombia, Italy, and Ecuador. 

</TEXT>

