<H3> <TI>   Fidel Castro Meets French Designer Cardin </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fidel Castro Meets French Designer Cardin </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL3105152394 Havana Radio Progreso Network in Spanish 1100 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3105152394 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Progreso Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Commander in Chief Fidel Castro Ruz has met Pierre 
Cardin, the acclaimed French designer, entrepreneur, and artist, 
and two of his associates at the Palace of the Revolution. 
Cardin told Fidel that he was fulfilling a longtime dream by 
visiting our country for the first time and by meeting him 
personally. Cardin also conveyed to the head of the revolution 
his enormous appreciation for all he had been able to see since 
his arrival in Havana, the capital's architecturally beautiful 
historical areas, the friendliness of the Cuban people, and 
Cuba's excellent conditions for developing international 
tourism. Fidel thanked Cardin for his visit and held a cordial 
and extensive exchange of ideas on issues related to the 
multifaceted activities of the French entrepreneur. 

</TEXT>

