<H3> <TI>   Reciprocal Investment Talks Begin With Spain </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reciprocal Investment Talks Begin With Spain </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2705010894 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1943 GMT 
26 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2705010894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Today, as part of the sixth joint economic 
commission of experts from Cuba and Spain, negotiations began 
for the establishment of an agreement that will promote and 
protect reciprocal investments. At the opening, Ernesto 
Melendez, minister of Foreign Investment and Economic 
Cooperation, described the relations with Spain as precious and 
important to Cuba. 
  Apolonio Ruiz Ligero, Spanish secretary of state for foreign 
trade, likewise pointed out that the information received on 
Cuba's economy is enlightening and that Madrid is attending this 
meeting with the hope of working with Cuba on problem solving. 
Melendez and Ruiz Lisgero head the specialized teams from their 
respective countries, which will analyze the possibilities for 
cooperation as part of the commission's work. 

</TEXT>

