<H3> <TI>   Fuel Unloading Pipeline System Under Construction </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Fuel Unloading Pipeline System Under Construction </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL2805111594 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1930 GMT 
27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2805111594 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Experts from different organizations are at the Moa 
port, in Holguin Province, to construct a pipeline system for 
unloading and storing fuel to reduce transport costs and to 
benefit the Cuban nickel industry. This fuel pipeline will be 
approximately one km in length. It will be built on Moa Bay and 
will include the coupling of tubes up to 24 inches in diameter 
and secured in a field away from the docks. This system will 
facilitate the unloading of fuel from tankers of up to 75,000 
tons in capacity which [words indistinct] the suppliers of fuel 
given the little depth of the old [word indistinct]. This 
complex work will allow the annual consumption of 300,000 tons 
of national crude oil by two of the three nickel plants and a 
cobalt plant which are operating in the northeastern part of 
Holguin. 

</TEXT>

