<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   `Antonio Guiteras' Power Plant Operational </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Antonio Guiteras' Power Plant Operational </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL3105152994 Havana Radio Reloj Network in Spanish 1402 GMT 
31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3105152994 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Reloj Network </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] After some technical difficulties, the Antonio 
Guiteras Power Plant in Matanzas has incorporated its 330 
megawatt unit into the national electric system. Specialists at 
that plant report that the average output exceeds 270 megawatts 
and that the recent repairs did away with other problems that 
obstructed the continuous generation of power. A one-month 
maintenance outage is projected for September, which will allow 
regulating 50 percent of the turbine valves, clean the boiler, 
and repair auxiliary equipment. 
  The Antonio Guiteras Electric Plant is the most efficient of 
its kind in Cuba and has achieved more than 40 percent of its 
electric production goals for 1994. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

