<H3> <TI>   Aristide Said To Side With France on Invasion </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Aristide Said To Side With France on Invasion </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   FL3105201494 Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio in French 1030 
GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL3105201494 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Signal FM Radio </F>
<F P=105>  French </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Jean-Claude Martineau has said Aristide will side 
with France and other countries so that he is not blamed for an 
invasion of Haiti. This weekend on a Montreal radio station, 
president-in-exile's spokesman detailed the avalanche strategy 
[strategie lavalassienne], in light of new developments in the 
Haitian crisis. He almost lost his temper in light of the 
pertinence of the questions of Compere Raymond Laurent, who had 
him unveil his government's priorities. Martineau clearly 
confessed that President Aristide will side with France and 
other countries so that he is not blamed for an invasion of 
Haiti. 

</TEXT>

