  [Text] The provisional government of attorney Emile 
Jonassaint has established an official agenda of meetings with 
the Senate office headed by Senator Bernard Sansaricq. The 
agenda notes that various provisional government ministers will 
have to appear before legislators to defend their management 
policy. The agenda, which lasts until 23 June, plans for an 
audience every two days at the Senate beginning 31 May. 
Information and Coordination Minister Jacques Saint-Louis will 
be the first guest of the Senate office headed by Bernard 
Sansaricq. Saint-Louis will be received by the Senate on 31 May. 

