<H3> <TI>   Cardenas Accepts Zedillo Invitation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Cardenas Accepts Zedillo Invitation </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PA2805140994 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2805140994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network 
in Spanish 1300 GMT 27 May 94 </F>

<F P=105> Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "Early Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Cuauhtemoc Cardenas, presidential candidate for the 
Party of the Democratic Revolution [PRD], said he accepts 
Ernesto Zedillo's invitation to hold a debate, but he insists 
that the initiative to hold a debate is his. 
  [Begin Cardenas recording] The candidate for the ruling 
party 
made a new invitation to the other candidates to participate in 
a debate of nine. The candidate for the ruling party seems to 
forget or does not want to listen to the other invitations made 
by other candidates, including myself, to hold a first debate 
among nine candidates. We hope it is not the only debate. The 
debates must not be regulated by the interest of the ruling 
candidate. It is time for the nine candidates, through their 
representatives, to reach an agreement on this next debate, but 
also on the other debates we may hold before 21 August. 
  I understand there should be at least three more debates 
among all candidates before 21 August. We also hope to hold 
debates among pairs of candidates. We hope all candidates can 
begin discussing this. It is not something the government or 
the Institutional Revolutionary Party candidate has to impose on 
us. It is something the candidates must agree upon amongst 
ourselves. We also have to reach agreements regarding the 
handling of the media following the debates, especially 
Televisa, Television Azteca, and Multivision. They should give 
all candidates the same opportunities to participate in what we 
may call a postdebate. This time should not be used as an 
opportunity to favor one or a few candidates to the detriment of 
the other candidates. These are the guidelines my 
representatives will be suggesting to the other candidates so 
that we can all reach an agreement and hold several debates 
before 21 August. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

