    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on Honduran economic developments monitored through 31 
May. 
  The Central Bank of Honduras has ordered private banks to 
transfer 50 percent of the foreign exchange they receive from 
export transactions to the Central Bank. This measure will 
worsen the liquidity situation experienced by the Honduran 
private banks. (Hamburg DPA in Spanish 1847 GMT 25 May 94) 
  The Honduran Government on 26 May ordered a freeze on the 
price of all petroleum byproducts. The measure is aimed at 
ensuring that distributors do not arbitrarily increase the price 
of these products. The freeze will continue in effect until 
further notice. (Tegucigalpa EL PERIODICO DE HONDURAS in Spanish 
27 May 94 p 5) 

