<H3> <TI>   Menem Says Alfonsin `Denied' Signing `Pact' With Alvarez </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Menem Says Alfonsin `Denied' Signing `Pact' With Alvarez </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY3105184794 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1224 GMT 31 May 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY3105184794 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>
<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 31 May (NA) -- President Carlos Menem 
announced this morning that Radical Civic Union leader Raul 
Alfonsin "last night denied" establishing a "pact" with Grand 
Front leader Carlos Chacho Alvarez to prevent the Justicialist 
Party from including a clause [in the constitutional reform] to 
allow the reelection of governors. 
  Menem told Radio 9.90: "We have only one pact here -- the 
Olivos Pact," which Menem signed with Alfonsin. 
  The chief of state did not hide his disquiet about some 
headlines in Buenos Aires newspapers which report an alleged 
"pact" between Alfonsin and Alvarez, or on the comparison he 
made between Argentina and Colombia [regarding the World Soccer 
Cup]. 

</TEXT>

