<F P=103> PY3105132494 </F>
<F P=104>  Sao Paulo AGENCIA ESTADO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Marco Antonio Moreira] </F>
  [Text] Belo Horizonte, 30 May (AE) -- Although President 
Itamar Franco has assured that his government will not get 
involved in the electoral campaign, Telerj [Rio de Janeiro 
Telephone Company] President Jose de Castro today announced that 
he will coordinate the presidential campaign of Brazilian Social 
Democracy Party candidate Fernando Henrique Cardoso. Telerj is 
a subsidiary of the state-owned company Telebras [Brazilian 
Telecommunications Inc.]. 
  De Castro is a member of the "Juiz de Fora group," which 
comprises President Franco's closest friends. He said he will 
hold an executive position in Cardoso's campaign and that he 
will serve as permanent liaison between Franco and Cardoso. 

</TEXT>

