p 1 </F>

<F P=103> PY2705031494 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] An electoral court on 25 May ordered an inquest to 
investigate if Luiz Inacio Lula da Silva, the Workers Party [PT] 
presidential candidate, violated the law when he used a sound 
truck from a union affiliated with the Sole Workers Center [CUT] 
in an election rally. Judge Alex Vilenozski ordered Lula, the 
PT, and the union to refrain from repeating this action and 
ordered the Civilian and Military Police to prevent the use of 
union equipment by presidential candidates in Sao Bernardo do 
Campo. Lula commented on the court ruling in Rio de Janeiro. 
  He said: Between what is legal and what is just, I believe 
the latter is more important. 

