<H3> <TI>   Admiral Goulart Fortuna Nominated PSC Presidential Candidate </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Admiral Goulart Fortuna Nominated PSC Presidential Candidate </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   PY3105205994 Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO in Portuguese 28 May 94 
p 10 </F>

<F P=103> PY3105205994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro O GLOBO </F>
<F P=105>  Portuguese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Admiral Henrique Goulart Fortuna yesterday announced 
his presidential candidacy for the PSC [Social Christian Party]. 
His platform should please the military, in light of his 
proposal to increase federal budget allocations for the Armed 
Forces from 2.7 percent to 5 percent. 
  The 60-year-old admiral served as commander of the War 
College from 1991 until his retirement in 1993. He joined the 
PSC in January with the intention of running for a federal 
deputy seat. Because it has become impossible for the PSC to 
nominate Senator Jose Sarney (Brazilian Democratic Movement 
Party) as its presidential candidate, the PSC has decided to 
promote Goulart Fortuna's candidacy. 
  Goulart Fortuna said: "The PSC national board has entrusted 
me with this mission, and I have accepted." 

</TEXT>

