  [Excerpts] Santa Fe de Bogota, 29 May (NOTIMEX) -- Official 
sources have reported Colombian President Cesar Gaviria today 
canceled his trip to El Salvador where he was to attend the 
swearing in ceremony of Salvadoran President-elect Armando 
Calderon Sol. Presidential Palace spokespersons have said the 
Colombian president will not attend the swearing in ceremony, 
because the doctors who performed surgery on his right foot 10 
days ago have recommended rest. [passage omitted] 
  Gaviria underwent surgery on 19 May to relieve pressure in 
his posterior tibial nerve. Using crutches, the Colombian 
president was the first to vote in Sunday's presidential 
elections, in which 18 candidates sought to become president of 
Colombia for the next four years. [passage omitted] 

