opportunity to improve relations between Colombia and Israel. 
[end recording] 
  This was part of the statements made by Shim'on Peres, 
architect of the Middle East peace process. He feels very 
satisfied and said he is confident that peace in the Middle East 
will be lasting. He intends to visit several voting tables; he 
will also visit the Gold Museum; and he will meet the president 
and they will issue a joint communique. This is the first visit 
Israeli foreign minister to Colombia. 

