<F P=105>  Spanish </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Israeli Foreign Minister Shim'on Peres said today 
that the world is moving toward an era of expanded markets and 
communities, adding that this is the moment for the awakening of 
the Americas. Peres, who arrived in Santa Fe de Bogota for an 
official two-day visit to Colombia, met with President Cesar 
Gaviria for 40 minutes. Peres congratulated Gaviria for being 
elected OAS secretary general, a position that the outgoing 
Colombian president will fill in September in replacement of 
Brazilian Joao Baena Soares. 
  The former Labor Party leader, whose first Latin American 
tour also includes Mexico and Chile, said his visit to Colombia 
is the result of the fortunate rapprochement that began in 
December with Colombian Foreign Minister Noemi Sanin de Rubio's 
visit to Israel. 

