BFN 

    [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic developments monitored through 31 May. 
  On 23 May, the Foreign Trade Institute reported that 
Colombian imports during the first four months of 1994 totaled 
$5.278 million. This represents a 22.7 percent increase over the 
same period last year. Imports of raw materials amounted to 
$2.1746 million -- 41.2 percent of all imports during the same 
